data.description: Welcome home to the beautiful Cypress Bay in Carolina Forest! Meticulous landscaping ushers you inside, where you'll be stunned by the living room with vaulted ceiling that showcases the home's split floor plan. Have large furniture? No problem! Whether you have several sitting pieces or a sectional, the living area is spacious enough to accommodate! One of the showstoppers of the home is the kitchen; whether you're a seasoned chef or a beginner, you'll be able to tackle any recipe! Stainless steel appliances, an abundance of cabinetry, backsplash for easy clean-up, bar top for extra chairs, a pantry for extra storage, and uninterrupted view to the dining area all make this space a chef's dream! Choose to enjoy a formal dining experience by the home's fireplace, or opt to create a new cozy sitting area. Down the hall are two ample-sized bedrooms and a full shared bathroom with shower/tub combo between them. On the other side of the living room is the oversized primary bedroom, which has been updated with board and batten accent wall and offers a spacious walk-in closet. Soak away all your stress in the en suite bathroom's soaking garden tub! Dual vanity sinks with granite countertops, a matching elongated mirror, and brushed nickel fixtures add modernity and ease to your morning routine. The walk-in shower has a sliding door and is encased by tile. Attached is the two-car garage, and extra space is available in the back yard shed. Whether you're in need of a night to yourself or are hosting others, the covered back deck and privacy-fenced back yard to the tree line is the perfect hangout spot! Beat the heat during the summer months by swimming in the community pool! Located just minutes away are local shopping centers, the hospital, restaurants, movie theaters, schools, area beaches, and military bases. Call today to schedule your showing!
